"""
Driver Framework — core trait + types shared by every OS driver and native lib.

@tag:stdlib
@tag:api

This module defines the contract that every Simple-language driver (kernel,
userspace, or native-lib) satisfies. A single `.spl` source can be built as
either (a) statically linked into the kernel or (b) packaged as a loadable
SMF library — the build profile picks. Pure-Simple drivers implement this
trait directly; C drivers reach the kernel only through an SFFI shim that
itself implements this trait.

Submodules:
  - core:         Driver trait (signatures only; no bodies).
  - types:        DriverClass, DriverStatus, ProbeResult, DeviceId, DriverHandle,
                  DriverContext, IoctlCmd.
  - error:        DriverError enum + errno_of() POSIX mapping.
  - manifest:     Manifest struct + .drv_manifest binary layout (DRVS section).
  - registry:     DriverRegistry + DriverOps function-pointer record.
  - static_table: Process-wide registry for static-mode drivers +
                  register_static_driver() helper.
  - loader:       .drv_manifest byte decoder + register_loaded() for
                  SMF-driven dynamic-mode loading.

Adopted design: pure-Simple-first; SFFI shim for legacy C drivers only.
See: doc/04_architecture/driver_architecture.md
Author guide: doc/07_guide/driver_authoring.md

Phase A (this commit): trait + types + error + design doc + author guide.
Phase B: attribute parsing, .drv_manifest section, kernel-side loader.
Phase C: DMA-coherent-alloc (6 arches), Cranelift >> fix, bitfield sugar.
Phase D: migrate fs_driver + gpu_driver + lld_ffi + cuda_ffi.
Phase E: migrate examples/simple_os/drivers/*.
"""

# All submodules are automatically available.
